data.enText: suitable or appropriate in the circumstances

data.chText: 特别恰当的描述 / 名字 / 评论

data.enText: likely or having a natural tendency to do sth

data.chText: 婴儿爱把东西往嘴里塞。
data.enText: Babies are apt to put objects into their mouths.
a person who has a natural ability to learn and understand

ex.enText: This kind of apple is apt to go bad.
Jack is apt to be impulsive.

synonyms.bx: 指天生具有做某事的倾向的，常后接动词不定式。

ex.chText: 这只狗生气时容易咬人。
ex.enText: The dog is liable to bite when angry.
This area is liable to flooding.
He is liable to catch a cold.

synonyms.bx: 只作表语，指因习惯或倾向性而易做某事或产生某种问题、患上某 种疾病等的，常后接动词不定式或介词 to。

ex.chText: 造成这个问题最有可能的原因是什么？
ex.enText: What is the most likely cause of the problem?

synonyms.bx: 指可能发生或属实的，强调可能性。

ex.enText: He is prone to be/being late.
My mother is prone to headaches.

ex.chText: 孩子大多喜欢吃垃圾食品。
ex.enText: Kids are mostly prone to eat junk food.

synonyms.bx: 尤指有发生不好或有害之事倾向的，通常作表语，常后接介词 to 或动词不定式。

tr: being of striking appropriateness and pertinence
example: the successful copywriter is a master of apposite and evocative verbal images
you are a clever man...you reason well and your wit is bold"-Bram Stoke

value.def: An apt remark, description, or choice is especially suitable.

example.ex: The words of this report are as apt today as in 1929.
example.tran: 这份报告的措词用在今天和用在1929年一样贴切。
对这种情况恰如其分的描述

value.tran: （话语、描述或选择）合适的，恰当的，贴切的

example.ex: ...the beach in the aptly named town of Oceanside.
example.tran: 名字起得十分贴切的海洋边镇的海滩

value.def: If someone is apt to do something, they often do it and so it is likely that they will do it again.

example.ex: She was apt to raise her voice and wave her hands about...
example.tran: 她动不动就拔高嗓门，并挥舞双手。

example.ex: This type of weather is apt to be more common in winter.
example.tran: 这种天气在冬季往往更为常见。

rootsaffixes.indicate: = to fit, ability 适应；能力
rootsaffixes.title: apt, ept

partsOfSpeech.dec: ad 加强 + apt 适应；能力 → 使适应，适应（环境）
ad 做… + apt 适应；能力 + able 有…能力的 → 有适应能力的
ad 做… + ept 适应；能力 → 有能力的 → 熟练的
apt 适应；能力 + itude 状态 → 适宜；才能
in 无 + apt 适应；能力 → 不适当的；不恰当的
in 无 + ept 适应；能力 → 不适宜的；无能的
in 无 + ept 适应；能力 + itude 表情况 → 无能
